-- Iran’s Ahmadinejad to Attend Mecca Summit Next Week, Office Says
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-08-06T08:22:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/iran-s-ahmadinejad-to-attend-mecca-summit-next-week-office-says.html
Iranian president  Mahmoud Ahmadinejad 
will take part in an Islamic solidarity summit in Mecca next
week following an invitation from Saudi Arabia’s  King Abdullah ,
the official  Islamic Republic News Agency  reported, citing the
president’s office.  Ahmadinejad will be present in the “emergency summit” on
Aug. 14-15 that’s aimed at reviewing developments in Arab
countries, Mohammad-Reza Forghani, director for international
affairs at Ahmadinejad’s office said, according to IRNA.  The kingdom invited leaders of the 57 member states of
Organization of Islamic Cooperation to attend the conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
